-- MetLife Discloses Second U.S. Investigative Demand in Loan Probe
-- B y   Z a c h a r y   T r a c e r
-- 2012-11-07T22:29:40Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-11-07/metlife-discloses-second-u-s-investigative-demand-in-loan-probe.html
MetLife Inc., the largest U.S. life
insurer, disclosed a second  U.S. Department of Justice  civil
investigative demand in a probe of origination or underwriting
of mortgages insured by the Federal Housing Administration.  The latest demand at the bank unit was received in
September, according to a regulatory filing today from the New
York-based insurer, which previously reported receiving one in
June.  To contact the reporter on this story:
